  "unmapped_findings": [
    "Density of Fe-Mn-Al-C steels reduces by up to 18% when Al content reaches 13 wt.%",
    "Single phase austenitic TWIP (SIMPLEX) steels have 25-30 wt.% Mn and <4-5 wt.% Al, deformation dominated by TWIP effect",
    "For Fe-20Mn-0.4C-xAl steels, increasing Al content increases yield strength and UTS but reduces elongation, mainly due to increasing ferrite content",
    "Fe-Mn-Al-C alloys exhibit specific energy absorption up to ~0.54 J/mm³, significantly higher than conventional deep-drawing steels",
    "Al increases stacking fault energy of Fe-Mn-Al-C steels, affecting twinning behavior and strain hardening characteristics",
    "Hydrogen charging reduces ductility of κ-carbide strengthened Fe-26Mn-11Al-1.2C steel due to planar slip localization promoted by κ-carbides"
  ]
